import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    sns.set_style("darkgrid")
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', data=data, color='blue')
    chart.axhline(y=data['price'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median Price: {:.2f}'.format(data['price'].median()))
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the trend of the S&P 500 index over the given time period?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['price'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the S&P 500 index prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Price')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data = data.groupby(['year', 'month']).mean().reset_index()
    data['return'] = data['price'].pct_change()
    ax = sns.barplot(x='month', y='return', data=data, color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=data['return'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Monthly Return')
    ax.set(xlabel='Month', ylabel='Average Monthly Return')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    sns.set(style="ticks")
    sp500 = data['price']
    other_indices = ['Dow Jones', 'Nasdaq', 'Russell 2000']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    for index in other_indices:
        ax.scatter(data['date'], data[index], label=index)
    ax.scatter(data['date'], sp500, label='S&P 500', color='black')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Index Value')
    ax.set_title('What is the correlation between the S&P 500 index and other major stock indices?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib.ticker import FuncFormatter

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(FuncFormatter(lambda x, _: '${:,.0f}'.format(x)))
    ax.set_title('What is the volatility of the S&P 500 index?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
